Selects a checkbox or radio button.
Element is located by label or name or CSS or XPath.

The second parameter is a context (CSS or XPath locator) to narrow the search.

```js
I.checkOption('#agree');
I.checkOption('I Agree to Terms and Conditions');
I.checkOption('agree', '//form');
// by ARIA locator
I.checkOption({ aria: 'Submit' });
```
@param {CodeceptJS.LocatorOrString} field checkbox located by label | name | CSS | XPath | ARIA | strict locator.
@param {?CodeceptJS.LocatorOrString} [context=null] (optional, `null` by default) element located by CSS | XPath | ARIA | strict locator.
@returns {void} automatically synchronized promise through #recorder

